arctgz(7)								   Miscellaneous Information Manual								    arctgz(7)

NAME
       arctgz - safety-first project lifecycle library for the arctgz archive format

SYNOPSIS
       use arctgz::{
	   init, load_config, save_config,
	   compile, extract, verify, diff, patch,
	   load_recipe, extract_recipe, execute_recipe,
	   ArctgzConfig, ArctgzManifest, FileEntry,
	   ArctgzRecipe, RecipeStep, Compression, Encryption,
	   ArctgzDelta, DeltaOp, ArctgzError
       };
       use std::path::Path;

       fn init(project_path: &Path, force: bool) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn load_config(project_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzConfig, ArctgzError>;
       fn save_config(project_path: &Path, config: &ArctgzConfig) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn compile(
	   project_path: &Path,
	   output_path: Option<&Path>,
	   force: bool,
	   private_key: Option<&[u8]>,
	   password: Option<&str>
       ) -> Result<PathBuf, ArctgzError>;
       fn extract(
	   archive_path: &Path,
	   output_dir: &Path,
	   force: bool,
	   public_key: Option<&[u8]>,
	   password: Option<&str>
       ) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn verify(
	   archive_path: &Path,
	   public_key: Option<&[u8]>,
	   password: Option<&str>
       ) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn diff(base: &Path, target: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzDelta, ArctgzError>;
       fn patch(
	   base: &Path, target: &Path, delta: &ArctgzDelta,
	   output_path: &Path, private_key: Option<&[u8]>
       ) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;
       fn load_recipe(project_path: &Path) -> Result<Option<ArctgzRecipe>, ArctgzError>;
       fn extract_recipe(archive_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzRecipe, ArctgzError>;
       fn execute_recipe(
	   output_dir: &Path,
	   recipe: &ArctgzRecipe,
	   force: bool
       ) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;

       struct ArctgzConfig {
	   pub name:	    String,
	   pub version:	    String,
	   pub include:	    Vec<String>,
	   pub compression: Compression,
	   pub encryption:  Encryption,
       }

       struct ArctgzManifest {
	   pub name:	    String,
	   pub version:	    String,
	   pub created:	    DateTime<Utc>,
	   pub compression: Compression,
	   pub files:	    BTreeMap<String, FileEntry>,
	   pub signature:   Option<String>,
       }

       struct FileEntry {
	   pub size:   u64,
	   pub sha512: String,
	   pub is_dir: bool,
       }

       struct ArctgzRecipe {
	   pub name:	String,
	   pub version: String,
	   pub steps:	Vec<RecipeStep>,
       }

       enum RecipeStep {
	   Copy	  { from: String, to: String },
	   MkDir  { path: String },
	   Chmod  { path: String, mode: String },
	   Remove { path: String },
       }

       enum Compression {
	   Gzip,
	   Zstd,
       }

       enum Encryption {
	   None,
	   Aes256Gcm,
       }

       struct ArctgzDelta {
	   pub base_name:	     String,
	   pub base_version:	     String,
	   pub target_name:	     String,
	   pub target_version:	     String,
	   pub base_manifest_hash:   String,
	   pub target_manifest_hash: String,
	   pub operations:	     Vec<DeltaOp>,
       }

       enum DeltaOp {
	   Add	   { path, size, sha512, is_dir },
	   Modify  { path, size, sha512, is_dir },
	   Delete  { path },
       }

       enum ArctgzError { ... }

DESCRIPTION
       The  arctgz  library provides a safe, cross-platform API for the full lifecycle of an arctgz project: scaffolding, configuration, compilation into a compressed and integrity-
       verified archive, verified extraction, standalone verification, post-extraction recipe execution, binary delta patching, and optional AES-256-GCM encryption.

       All operations enforce strict path confinement, validate metadata before touching the filesystem, and use atomic file operations to prevent corruption  and  TOCTOU  (time-of-
       check to time-of-use) races.

       The core functionality includes:

       • init() – scaffold a new project directory with a default configuration and an empty resource folder.

       • load_config() / save_config() – read and write validated project configuration.

       • compile()  –  create  a  compressed archive (gzip or zstd) with SHA-512 hashes and a manifest; supports parallel hashing, glob includes, empty directories, optional Ed25519
	 signatures, and optional AES-256-GCM encryption.

       • extract() – unpack an archive with full integrity checks, path traversal prevention, and automatic decryption if needed.

       • verify() – check archive integrity without writing files; also verifies optional signatures and decrypts if needed.

       • diff() / patch() – create and apply binary deltas for efficient updates between archive versions.

       • load_recipe() / extract_recipe() / execute_recipe() – manage and execute post-extraction recipes (copy, mkdir, chmod, remove).

       All paths are resolved with std::fs::canonicalize() (equivalent to realpath(3)), so symbolic links are followed during the home-directory confinement check.  The  library  is
       fully tested on Linux, macOS, and Windows.

INSTALLATION
       This man page can be installed system-wide using the provided installer script:

       curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash

       The script places arctgz.7 into /usr/local/share/man/man7/ and updates the man database.	 To uninstall, run:

       curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash -s -- uninstall

FUNCTIONS
       init(project_path, force)
	      Initialises a new arctgz project at project_path.	 Creates the directory, an include/ subdirectory, and a default arctgz.init file.  The default configuration includes
	      "compression": "gzip" and "encryption": "None".  See ArctgzConfig for details.

       Security checks are performed before any filesystem changes; a failed call leaves no side effects.

       load_config(project_path)
	      Reads and validates arctgz.init.

       save_config(project_path, config)
	      Atomically writes a validated ArctgzConfig back to disk (temp file + rename).

       compile(project_path, output_path, force, private_key, password)
	      Compiles the project into an .artgz archive.

       output_path specifies the exact output file; if None, defaults to project_path/archive.artgz.

       force controls overwriting an existing file.

       If private_key is provided (32-byte Ed25519 secret key), the manifest is signed and the signature embedded in the archive.

       If the configuration's encryption field is set to Aes256Gcm, password must be supplied; the final archive is encrypted with AES-256-GCM using an Argon2-derived key.

       Include	patterns  may  contain glob wildcards (e.g. *.txt, assets/**/*.png).  Empty directories that match a pattern are preserved as directory entries in the archive.	 Sym‐
       links are rejected.

       extract(archive_path, output_dir, force, public_key, password)
	      Extracts an archive with full verification.  Compression is detected automatically; encrypted archives are decrypted on the fly if password is correct.  If  public_key
	      is  provided,  the  manifest  signature is verified before extraction.  Path traversal (absolute paths, .., empty, .) is rejected.  Existing files are overwritten only
	      when force is true.

       verify(archive_path, public_key, password)
	      Standalone integrity check.  Validates every file's hash and size, ensures manifest consistency, checks for unsafe paths, and optionally verifies a signature  and  de‐
	      crypts the archive.  No files are written.

       diff(base_archive, target_archive)
	      Computes	a  binary  delta  between two archives.	 Returns an ArctgzDelta containing the minimal set of Add, Modify, and Delete operations needed to transform the base
	      archive into the target.	Metadata files (arctgz.init, recipe.json) are ignored during comparison.

       patch(base, target, delta, output_path, private_key)
	      Applies a previously computed delta to the base archive, producing a new archive that is bit-for-bit identical to the original target.  The base's unchanged files  are
	      copied directly; modified or added files are taken from the target archive.  If private_key is provided, the new manifest is signed.

       load_recipe(project_path)
	      Loads and validates recipe.json from a project directory. Returns Ok(None) if absent.

       extract_recipe(archive_path)
	      Extracts and validates the embedded recipe.json from an archive (gzip/zstd/encrypted transparently).

       execute_recipe(output_dir, recipe, force)
	      Runs the steps of a recipe inside output_dir.  Supported steps: Copy, MkDir, Chmod (Unix only; returns RecipeExecutionError on other platforms), Remove.	All paths are
	      validated; absolute, .., empty, and . are rejected.  When force is false, existing files/directories cause an error.

TYPES
       ArctgzConfig
	      Project configuration stored in arctgz.init.

	      name   Project name (alphanumeric, -, _; max 255 chars).

	      version
		     Semantic version string.

	      include
		     List of relative resource paths or glob patterns (max 100 entries).

	      compression
		     "gzip" (default) or "zstd".

	      encryption
		     "None" (default) or "Aes256Gcm".

       The configuration file uses strict JSON validation; unknown fields are rejected.

       ArctgzManifest
	      Embedded in every archive as manifest.json.

	      name, version
		     Copied from config.

	      created
		     UTC timestamp of compilation.

	      compression
		     Algorithm used for this archive.

	      files  BTreeMap from archive paths to FileEntry.

	      signature
		     Optional hex-encoded Ed25519 signature over the manifest (with this field set to None before signing).

       FileEntry
	      Metadata for one file: size (u64), sha512 hex string, and is_dir (bool).

       ArctgzRecipe
	      Describes post-extraction actions.

	      name, version
		     Recipe identity.

	      steps  Ordered list of RecipeStep.

       RecipeStep
	      Enum with Copy, MkDir, Chmod, Remove.

       Compression
	      Enum: Gzip, Zstd.

       Encryption
	      Enum: None, Aes256Gcm.

       ArctgzDelta
	      Describes the difference between two archives.

       DeltaOp
	      Enum: Add, Modify, Delete. Each carries path, size, SHA-512, and an is_dir flag (except Delete).

       ArctgzError
	      All failure variants, now including SignatureError, KeyError, DeltaError, and EncryptionError.

EXAMPLE
   Initialising a project with zstd compression and encryption
       use arctgz::{init, load_config, save_config, Compression, Encryption};

       fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
	   let project = Path::new("./my-project");
	   init(project, false)?;
	   let mut cfg = load_config(project)?;
	   cfg.compression = Compression::Zstd;
	   cfg.encryption = Encryption::Aes256Gcm;
	   save_config(project, &cfg)?;
	   Ok(())
       }

   Compile, sign, verify and extract an encrypted archive
       use arctgz::{compile, verify, extract};
       let archive = compile(project, None, false, Some(&private_key), Some("secret"))?;
       verify(&archive, Some(&public_key), Some("secret"))?;
       let out = Path::new("/tmp/out");
       extract(&archive, out, false, Some(&public_key), Some("secret"))?;

   Creating and applying a delta
       use arctgz::{diff, patch};
       let delta = diff(&base_archive, &target_archive)?;
       let output = Path::new("./update.artgz");
       patch(&base_archive, &target_archive, &delta, output, None)?;

FILES
       arctgz.init
	      Project configuration (JSON). Strict validation; unknown fields rejected.

       include/
	      Resource directory (source of archived files).

       recipe.json (optional)
	      Post-extraction recipe.

       <output>.artgz
	      The compiled (and optionally encrypted) archive.

ENVIRONMENT
       HOME (Unix) / USERPROFILE (Windows)
	      Home directory used for path confinement (via dirs crate).

SECURITY
       • Home-directory confinement for init.

       • No side effects before validation.

       • Atomic writes (config, archive).

       • Archive integrity via SHA-512 manifest (hash and size).

       • Ed25519 signature verification (optional).

       • AES-256-GCM encryption with Argon2 key derivation (optional).

       • Path traversal prevention in extraction, verification, and recipes.

       • Symlink rejection during compilation.

       • Strict JSON validation (deny unknown fields) for configuration and recipes.

NOTES
       The library does not provide internal locking; concurrent operations on the same project may lead to races.  Every individual write operation is atomic, so partial corruption
       is avoided.

VERSION
       arctgz 0.8.0 – adds AES-256-GCM encryption, binary delta patching, glob-based include patterns, empty directory preservation, and a revised compilation API with direct output
       path and password support.

SEE ALSO
       semver(7), realpath(3), serde_json(5), dirs(7), flate2(7), zstd(1), tar(5), sha2(7), rayon(7), ed25519-dalek(7), aes-gcm(7), argon2(7)

BUGS
       • The include/ directory is always empty initially; files must be added manually.

       • No cryptographic signatures for encrypted archives beyond the inner Ed25519 manifest signature; encryption provides confidentiality but not non-repudiation.

       • Chmod step is not supported on non-Unix platforms and returns an error.

